Class LuceneGlobalDocumentsTree

java.lang.Object
  com.nsp.search.utils.LuceneGlobalDocumentsTree

public class LuceneGlobalDocumentsTree
extends java.lang.Object

LuceneFundsTree ideally should ONLY search funds and find ones that have parents - that way you get no dead ends 2 ways to do this - query parents and then see if parents have children (this way you do many child lookups) or query children and aggregate parents (that way you ONLY do 1 lookup across children
